---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Found in Space"
	description="Found in Space is an educational platform for exploring, understanding, and building with Gaia-based data of the solar neighbourhood."
>
	<header class="site-header">
		<a class="wordmark" href="/" aria-label="Found in Space home">
			<span class="wordmark__mark" aria-hidden="true"></span>
			<span class="wordmark__text">
				<span class="wordmark__title">Found in Space</span>
				<span class="wordmark__meta">Solar neighbourhood platform</span>
			</span>
		</a>
		<nav class="site-nav" aria-label="Primary">
			<a href="#explore">Explore</a>
			<a href="#learn">Learn</a>
			<a href="#build">Build</a>
			<a href="#about">About</a>
		</nav>
	</header>

	<main class="page">
		<section class="hero">
			<p class="eyebrow">Gaia data, public understanding, and the solar neighbourhood</p>
			<h1>A platform for learning space through data, perspective, and interaction.</h1>
			<p class="intro">
				Found in Space turns astronomical data into an educational experience. It begins with the
				stars around us, draws on Gaia's map of the solar neighbourhood, and opens that material up
				for exploration, explanation, and new ways of building with it.
			</p>
			<div class="hero__actions">
				<a class="button button--primary" href="#explore">Start exploring</a>
				<a class="button button--ghost" href="#build">See the stack</a>
			</div>
			<div class="hero__note">
				<p>
					The site is being shaped as an educational platform rather than a project brochure: part
					exhibit, part classroom, part lab.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="section-grid" aria-label="Core routes">
			<article class="panel panel--accent" id="explore">
				<p class="panel__eyebrow">Explore</p>
				<h2>Begin with the sky as people know it, then reveal the structure beneath it.</h2>
				<p>
					Guided journeys will use an interactive star map to move from familiar patterns such as
					constellations into depth, distance, scale, and stellar neighbourhoods.
				</p>
			</article>
			<article class="panel" id="learn">
				<p class="panel__eyebrow">Learn</p>
				<h2>Support curiosity with clear concepts, activities, and teaching routes.</h2>
				<p>
					Found in Space is being designed for self-directed learners, teachers, and students who
					need more than spectacle. The aim is understanding, not just interaction.
				</p>
			</article>
			<article class="panel" id="build">
				<p class="panel__eyebrow">Build</p>
				<h2>Show how catalogue data becomes an explorable 3D environment.</h2>
				<p>
					Behind the experience sits a pipeline, an octree, and a browser-based viewer. The site
					will explain that stack in human terms and make the technical work reusable.
				</p>
			</article>
		</section>

		<section class="story">
			<div class="story__lead">
				<p class="eyebrow">Why this project exists</p>
				<h2>The night sky is familiar. Its structure is not.</h2>
			</div>
			<div class="story__body">
				<p>
					Most people meet astronomy through images, headlines, or the visible sky. Found in Space
					starts there, but does not stop there. It asks what becomes possible when the solar
					neighbourhood is not only seen, but explored as data.
				</p>
				<p>
					The project is grounded in Gaia, but its purpose is educational and public-facing: to
					create routes from recognition to understanding, and from wonder to inquiry.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="bands">
			<article class="band">
				<p class="band__label">First journey</p>
				<h3>What constellations hide about 3D space</h3>
				<p>
					A familiar sky pattern becomes the entry point for perspective, measurement, and the fact
					that stars which seem adjacent from Earth may be widely separated in space.
				</p>
			</article>
			<article class="band">
				<p class="band__label">Launch shape</p>
				<h3>Three routes into the platform</h3>
				<p>
					`Explore` for guided experiences, `Learn` for structured explanation, and `Build` for the
					technical architecture and open project layer.
				</p>
			</article>
		</section>

		<section class="about" id="about">
			<p class="eyebrow">About</p>
			<h2>Independent, but connected.</h2>
			<p>
				Found in Space will live as its own platform while remaining lightly connected to
				<a href="https://www.k-si.com/">k-si.com</a>. The intention is for this site to explain the
				project itself: what it makes possible, how it works, and why it matters educationally.
			</p>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	.site-header {
		position: sticky;
		top: 0;
		z-index: 4;
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: space-between;
		gap: 1rem;
		max-width: calc(var(--fis-max-width) + 3rem);
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 1rem 1.5rem 0;
		background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(7, 17, 31, 0.88), rgba(7, 17, 31, 0));
		backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
	}

	.wordmark {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.85rem;
		padding: 0.65rem 0.85rem;
		border-radius: 999px;
		background: rgba(8, 15, 27, 0.68);
		border: 1px solid var(--fis-line);
		box-shadow: var(--fis-shadow);
		text-decoration: none;
	}

	.wordmark__mark {
		position: relative;
		width: 2.25rem;
		height: 2.25rem;
		border-radius: 999px;
		background:
			radial-gradient(circle at 35% 35%, #fff6d8 0, #f2c879 24%, #a75b2f 56%, rgba(167, 91, 47, 0) 58%),
			radial-gradient(circle at center, rgba(141, 183, 255, 0.14), transparent 70%);
		box-shadow:
			0 0 0 1px rgba(242, 200, 121, 0.16),
			0 0 32px rgba(141, 183, 255, 0.16);
	}

	.wordmark__mark::after {
		content: '';
		position: absolute;
		inset: -0.32rem;
		border: 1px solid rgba(141, 183, 255, 0.35);
		border-radius: 999px;
		transform: rotate(-18deg);
	}

	.wordmark__text {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.1rem;
	}

	.wordmark__title {
		font-size: 1rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.08em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--fis-gold);
	}

	.wordmark__meta {
		font-size: 0.78rem;
		color: var(--fis-text-muted);
	}

	.site-nav {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 0.55rem;
		font-size: 0.96rem;
	}

	.site-nav a {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		min-height: 2.55rem;
		padding: 0.55rem 0.9rem;
		border-radius: 999px;
		background: rgba(8, 15, 27, 0.62);
		border: 1px solid rgba(141, 183, 255, 0.14);
		color: var(--fis-text-soft);
		text-decoration: none;
		transition:
			transform 160ms ease,
			background-color 160ms ease,
			border-color 160ms ease,
			color 160ms ease;
	}

	.site-nav a:hover {
		transform: translateY(-1px);
		background: rgba(15, 28, 50, 0.82);
		border-color: rgba(242, 200, 121, 0.32);
		color: var(--fis-text);
	}

	.page {
		position: relative;
		min-height: 100vh;
		max-width: var(--fis-max-width);
		padding: 3.5rem 1.5rem 5rem;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.eyebrow {
		margin: 0 0 1rem;
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.18em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--fis-gold);
	}

	.hero {
		padding: 4.2rem 0 2.4rem;
	}

	h1,
	h2,
	h3 {
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: -0.03em;
	}

	h1 {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 6.25rem);
		line-height: 0.95;
		max-width: 12ch;
	}

	.intro {
		max-width: 46rem;
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: var(--fis-text-soft);
		margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
	}

	.hero__actions {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 0.85rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.button {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		min-height: 2.9rem;
		padding: 0.75rem 1.15rem;
		border-radius: 999px;
		text-decoration: none;
		font-size: 0.98rem;
		transition:
			transform 160ms ease,
			box-shadow 160ms ease,
			border-color 160ms ease;
	}

	.button:hover {
		transform: translateY(-1px);
	}

	.button--primary {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f2c879 0%, #f3deac 100%);
		color: #0d1524;
		box-shadow: 0 16px 30px rgba(242, 200, 121, 0.18);
	}

	.button--ghost {
		border: 1px solid var(--fis-line-strong);
		background: rgba(9, 18, 33, 0.5);
		color: var(--fis-text);
	}

	.hero__note,
	.panel,
	.band,
	.about {
		background: var(--fis-panel);
		border: 1px solid var(--fis-line);
		border-radius: var(--fis-radius);
		backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
		box-shadow: var(--fis-shadow);
	}

	.hero__note {
		max-width: 36rem;
		padding: 1.05rem 1.15rem;
		border-color: rgba(141, 183, 255, 0.16);
	}

	.section-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 1rem;
		margin: 2rem 0 4rem;
	}

	.panel {
		padding: 1.45rem;
	}

	.panel--accent {
		background:
			linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(242, 200, 121, 0.12), rgba(10, 20, 36, 0.78)),
			var(--fis-panel);
	}

	.panel__eyebrow,
	.band__label {
		margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.16em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--fis-gold);
	}

	.story {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.1fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
		gap: 2rem;
		align-items: start;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}

	.story__lead h2 {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.2rem);
		line-height: 1.02;
		max-width: 11ch;
	}

	.story__body {
		padding-top: 0.35rem;
	}

	.bands {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 1rem;
		margin-bottom: 4rem;
	}

	.band {
		padding: 1.45rem;
		background: var(--fis-panel-strong);
	}

	.about {
		padding: 1.6rem;
		max-width: 48rem;
	}

	h2 {
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
		font-size: 1.75rem;
		line-height: 1.1;
	}

	h3 {
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
		font-size: 1.4rem;
		line-height: 1.15;
	}

	p {
		margin: 0;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: var(--fis-text-soft);
	}

	section p + p {
		margin-top: 1rem;
	}

	.about a {
		color: var(--fis-gold);
		text-decoration-color: rgba(242, 200, 121, 0.46);
	}

	@media (max-width: 900px) {
		.section-grid,
		.story,
		.bands {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.story__lead h2 {
			max-width: none;
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.site-header {
			align-items: flex-start;
			flex-direction: column;
			padding-bottom: 0.25rem;
		}

		.page {
			padding-top: 2.25rem;
		}

		h1 {
			font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 14vw, 4.2rem);
		}

		h2 {
			font-size: 1.5rem;
		}

		.intro {
			font-size: 1.05rem;
		}
	}
</style>
